.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_DeviceFinder
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Device Finder offers a collection of static methods that can be called to find common game devices such as the headset or controllers, or used to determine key information about the connected devices.

methods.name: DeviceTransform(Devices device)
methods.summary: The DeviceTransform method returns the transform for a given Devices enum.
methods.returns: The transform for the given Devices enum.

params.value: The Devices enum to get the transform for.

methods.name: GetActualController(GameObject givenController)
methods.summary: The GetActualController method will attempt to get the actual SDK controller object.
methods.returns: The GameObject that is the actual controller.

params.value: The GameObject of the controller.

methods.name: GetControllerAngularVelocity(GameObject givenController)
methods.summary: The GetControllerAngularVelocity method is used for getting the current rotational velocity of the physical game controller. This can be useful for determining which way the controller is being rotated and at what speed the rotation is occurring.
methods.returns: A 3 dimensional vector containing the current real world physical controller angular (rotational) velocity.

params.value: The GameObject of the controller.

methods.name: GetControllerAngularVelocity(VRTK_ControllerReference controllerReference)
methods.summary: The GetControllerAngularVelocity method is used for getting the current rotational velocity of the physical game controller. This can be useful for determining which way the controller is being rotated and at what speed the rotation is occurring.
methods.returns: A 3 dimensional vector containing the current real world physical controller angular (rotational) velocity.

params.value: The reference to the controller.

methods.name: GetControllerByIndex(uint index, bool getActual)
methods.summary: The GetControllerByIndex method is used to find a controller based on it's unique index.
methods.returns: The actual controller GameObject that matches the given index.

params.value: The index of the actual controller to find.
An optional parameter that if true will return the game object that the SDK controller is attached to.

methods.syntax: public static GameObject GetControllerByIndex(uint index, bool getActual)
methods.linkedSyntax: public static GameObject GetControllerByIndex(uint index, bool getActual)

methods.name: GetControllerHand(GameObject controller)
methods.summary: The GetControllerHand method is used for getting the enum representation of ControllerHand for the given controller game object.
methods.returns: A ControllerHand representing either the Left or Right hand.

params.value: The controller game object to check the hand of.

methods.name: GetControllerHandType(string hand)
methods.summary: The GetControllerHandType method is used for getting the enum representation of ControllerHand from a given string.
methods.returns: A ControllerHand representing either the Left or Right hand.

params.value: The string representation of the hand to retrieve the type of. left or right.

methods.name: GetControllerIndex(GameObject controller)
methods.summary: The GetControllerIndex method is used to find the index of a given controller object.
methods.returns: The index of the given controller.

params.value: The controller object to get the index of a controller.

methods.name: GetControllerLeftHand(bool getActual)
methods.summary: The GetControllerLeftHand method retrieves the game object for the left hand controller.
methods.returns: The left hand controller.

params.value: An optional parameter that if true will return the game object that the SDK controller is attached to.

methods.name: GetControllerOrigin(GameObject controller)
methods.summary: The GetControllerOrigin method is used to find the controller's origin.
methods.returns: The transform of the controller origin or if an origin is not set then the transform parent.

params.value: The GameObject to get the origin for.

methods.name: GetControllerOrigin(VRTK_ControllerReference controllerReference)
methods.summary: The GetControllerOrigin method is used to find the controller's origin.
methods.returns: The transform of the controller origin or if an origin is not set then the transform parent.

params.value: The reference to the controller to get the origin for.

methods.name: GetControllerRightHand(bool getActual)
methods.summary: The GetControllerRightHand method retrieves the game object for the right hand controller.
methods.returns: The right hand controller.

params.value: An optional parameter that if true will return the game object that the SDK controller is attached to.

methods.name: GetControllerVelocity(GameObject givenController)
methods.summary: The GetControllerVelocity method is used for getting the current velocity of the physical game controller. This can be useful to determine the speed at which the controller is being swung or the direction it is being moved in.
methods.returns: A 3 dimensional vector containing the current real world physical controller velocity.

params.value: The GameObject of the controller.

methods.name: GetControllerVelocity(VRTK_ControllerReference controllerReference)
methods.summary: The GetControllerVelocity method is used for getting the current velocity of the physical game controller. This can be useful to determine the speed at which the controller is being swung or the direction it is being moved in.
methods.returns: A 3 dimensional vector containing the current real world physical controller velocity.

params.value: The reference to the controller.

methods.name: GetCurrentControllerType()
methods.summary: The GetCurrentControllerType method returns the current used ControllerType based on the SDK and headset being used.
methods.returns: The ControllerType based on the SDK and headset being used.

methods.name: GetHeadsetAngularVelocity()
methods.summary: The GetHeadsetAngularVelocity method is used to determine the current angular velocity of the headset.
methods.returns: A Vector3 containing the current angular velocity of the headset.

methods.name: GetHeadsetType(bool summary)
methods.summary: The GetHeadsetType method returns the type of headset connected to the computer.
methods.returns: The Headset type that is connected.

params.value: If this is true, then the generic name for the headset is returned not including the version type (e.g. OculusRift will be returned for DK2 and CV1).

methods.name: GetHeadsetVelocity()
methods.summary: The GetHeadsetVelocity method is used to determine the current velocity of the headset.
methods.returns: A Vector3 containing the current velocity of the headset.

methods.name: GetModelAliasController(GameObject givenController)
methods.summary: The GetModelAliasController method will attempt to get the object that contains the model for the controller.
methods.returns: The GameObject that is the alias controller containing the controller model.

params.value: The GameObject of the controller.

methods.name: GetModelAliasControllerHand(GameObject givenObject)
methods.summary: The GetModelAliasControllerHand method will return the hand that the given model alias GameObject is for.
methods.returns: The enum of the ControllerHand that the given GameObject may represent.

params.value: The GameObject that may represent a model alias.

methods.name: GetScriptAliasController(GameObject givenController)
methods.summary: The GetScriptAliasController method will attempt to get the object that contains the scripts for the controller.
methods.returns: The GameObject that is the alias controller containing the scripts.

params.value: The GameObject of the controller.

methods.name: HeadsetCamera()
methods.summary: The HeadsetCamera method is used to retrieve the transform for the VR Camera in the scene.
methods.returns: The transform of the VR Camera component.

methods.name: HeadsetTransform()
methods.summary: The HeadsetTransform method is used to retrieve the transform for the VR Headset in the scene. It can be useful to determine the position of the user's head in the game world.
methods.returns: The transform of the VR Headset component.

methods.name: IsControllerLeftHand(GameObject checkController)
methods.summary: The IsControllerLeftHand method is used to check if a given controller game object is the left handed controller.
methods.returns: Is true if the given controller is the left controller.

params.value: The controller object that is being checked.

methods.name: IsControllerOfHand(GameObject checkController, ControllerHand hand)
methods.summary: The IsControllerOfHand method is used to check if a given controller game object is of the hand type provided.
methods.returns: Is true if the given controller matches the given hand.

params.value: The actual controller object that is being checked.
The representation of a hand to check if the given controller matches.

methods.syntax: public static bool IsControllerOfHand(GameObject checkController, ControllerHand hand)
methods.linkedSyntax: public static bool IsControllerOfHand(GameObject checkController, ControllerHand hand)

methods.name: IsControllerRightHand(GameObject checkController)
methods.summary: The IsControllerRightHand method is used to check if a given controller game object is the right handed controller.
methods.returns: Is true if the given controller is the right controller.

params.value: The controller object that is being checked.

methods.name: PlayAreaTransform()
methods.summary: The PlayAreaTransform method is used to retrieve the transform for the play area in the scene.
methods.returns: The transform of the VR Play Area component.
